HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 256
By Powers
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Tracy Adkins Powers
upon her receipt of the 2025 Great Smoky
Mountain Council Outstanding Educator Award.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should salute those
citizens who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as community
leaders of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy person is Tracy Adkins Powers, who is being honored
with the 2025 Outstanding Educator Award by the Great Smoky Mountain Council of the Boy
Scouts of America for her exceptional service to education in Campbell County and support and
promotion of Scouting; and
WHEREAS, the award was established in 2017 by the Educational Relationships
Subcommittee of the National Council of Scouting America, and Mrs. Powers is the seventh
recipient of the Elbert K. Fretwell Award for exceptional service to education; she will receive
this prestigious award at the Campbell County Good Scout Award Dinner on March 13, 2025, at
the Ball Farm Event Center in LaFollette; and
WHEREAS, a Campbell County native, Tracy Powers is the daughter of William and
Fleda Adkins and was raised on a farm in Jacksboro with her two brothers and two sisters; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Powers attended both Jacksboro Elementary School and Jacksboro
Middle School before graduating from Campbell County High School; she received a Bachelor
of Science degree in Education from Liberty University and later earned a master's degree from
the University of Tennessee; and
