WHEREAS, after college, Tracy Powers married State Representative Dennis Powers
and began her teaching career in Knox County; she later returned to Campbell County and
taught at Jacksboro Middle School; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Powers was hired as a site director at Roane State Community
College Campbell County Center in 1997 and went on to play an instrumental role in the
development of two cutting-edge science laboratories, an elegant library extension, and a
vibrant student center, all the while witnessing the transformative journeys of countless students
as they completed their education and emerged as accomplished men and women; and
WHEREAS, having retired in 2023, Tracy Powers continues to make significant
contributions to her community; she remains actively involved at her church, First Baptist
Jacksboro, and serves on the LaFollette Hospital Board; she also enjoys traveling with her
husband and cherishing moments with her family, particularly her great-nieces and -nephews;
and
WHEREAS, through her estimable service to Campbell County, Mrs. Powers epitomizes
the spirit and commitment that are characteristic of a true Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud Tracy Powers for her
dedication to the State of Tennessee and its citizens; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Tracy Adkins Powers upon her receipt of the
2025 Great Smoky Mountain Council Outstanding Educator Award, thank her for her meritorious
service to Campbell County and this State, and extend to her our best wishes for every future
success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
